%N A167179 The number of additional armies one receives in Parker Brothers' (now part of Hasbro) game of Risk for turning in the n-th set of three different or alike cards.
%C A167179 Although this sequence is theoretically infinite, in actual practice, terms greater than a(15) are rarely reached.
%H A167179 Hasbro, <a href="http://www.hasbro.com/common/instruct/risk.pdf">Rules of Risk</a>
%H A167179 Wikipedia, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk_%28game%29#Turning_in_Risk_cards">Risk game</a>
%H A167179 <a href="/index/Rec#order_02">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (2,-1).
%F A167179 a(n) = 2*(n+1) for n<=5, otherwise a(n) = 5*(n-3).
%t A167179 LinearRecurrence[{2, -1}, {4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 15, 20}, 50] (* _G. C. Greubel_, Jun 04 2016; amended by _Georg Fischer_, Apr 03 2019 *)
